Hungary’s BUX Stock Index Rises From Eight-Month Low; OTP Jumps

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-04T07:15:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/hungary-s-bux-stock-index-rises-from-eight-month-low-otp-jumps.html
Hungary’s benchmark stock index rose
from an eight-month low, ending a three-day selloff, as OTP Bank
Nyrt., the country’s largest lender, advanced.  The BUX gauge of 13 companies added as much as 0.7 percent
and traded up 0.4 percent at 20,608.91 as of 9:09 a.m. in
Budapest. OTP, which has a 29 percent weighting in the index,
jumped 1.9 percent to 4,940 forint.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  